<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7484> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7484" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Cos. 77. Praetor by 80. See MRR 2.80. Noting the age of his father, Brutus Callaicus (57). Cos. 138, Sumner suggests that his career, as in many other cases, was delayed during the wars, so that the praetorship should probably be dated before 90 (Orators 103-104).\n" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4305> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4305" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Cic. Brut. 175; Sall. Hist. 3.48.10M; Fast. Cap., Degrassi 56f., 130, 484f. (Brutus' name entire; Mam. [Ai]miliu[s Mam. f. - n. Lepi]d. Livia[nus]); Ascon. 81C; Obseq. 58; Chr. 354 (Mamereo et Iuliano); Fast. Hyd. (Bruto et Mamereo); so also Chr. Pasc.; Cassiod.; and on Lepidus, Cic. Off. 2.-58; Cluent. 99; Val. Max. 7.7.6." .
